  <brief_title>Antimicrobial Hernia Repair Device Clinical Study</brief_title>
  <acronym>AMEX</acronym>
  <official_title>Feasibility Study of the Antimicrobial Hernia Repair Device for Repair of Ventral or Incisional Hernia</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Cook Group Incorporated</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Cook Group Incorporated</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This prospective clinical study will evaluate the safety and efficacy of the Cook速
      Antimicrobial Hernia Repair Device containing an antimicrobial to reinforce soft tissue
      during ventral or incisional hernia repair in clean-contaminated, contaminated, and
      dirty-infected (i.e., Class II, Class III, and Class IV) surgical fields. Up to 30 patients
      will be treated with the Cook速 Antimicrobial Hernia Repair Device and patients will be
      followed for 12 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
