  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient presents with a ventral or incisional hernia that is to be surgically
             corrected using open repair technique

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Body Mass Index (BMI) &lt; 25.

          -  Body weight &lt; 45 kg

          -  Glycosylated Hemoglobin (Hgb A1c) &gt; 10%

          -  Albumin &lt; 2.5 g/dL or pre-albumin &lt; 5.0 mg/dL

          -  Renal insufficiency, as determined by an estimated glomerular filtration rate (GFR) &lt;
             60 mL/min/1.73 m2

          -  Known allergies to study device components

          -  Other relevant exclusion criteria apply
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
